comments: Booker (PHX) makes marginal contact to Crowder (MEM) and doesn't affect his SQBR or ability to pass.
Rubio (PHX) makes marginal contact with Clarke (MEM) and doesn't affect his SQBR at the start of his drive.
Brooks (MEM) cleanly dislodges the ball from Oubre Jr. (PHX) at the end of his drive.
Crowder (MEM) and Bridges (PHX) engage and separate during the screen.
Rubio (PHX) makes incidental contact with Morant (MEM) in the backcourt and doesn't affect his SQBR.
Crowder (MEM) brushes Booker's (PHX) off-arm and doesn't affect his shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) extends his off-arm into Booker's (PHX) head during his drive and affects his ability to defend.
Crowder (MEM) establishes himself in Booker's (PHX) path off-ball and absorbs the contact.
Crowder (MEM) makes contact to Booker's (PHX) arm and affects his SQBR. The contact occurs prior to his upward shooting motion.
Rubio (PHX) makes marginal contact as he brushes Morant's (MEM) off-arm during his pass in the backcourt.
Crowder (MEM) makes contact to Bridges' (PHX) arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Bridges (PHX) makes marginal contact with Melton's (MEM) arm at the start of his drive and doesn't knock him off his direct path.
Bridges (PHX) makes contact with Melton's (MEM) arm during his upward shooting motion that affects the play at the basket.
Oubre Jr. (PHX) establishes himself in Crowder's (MEM) path during the off-ball screen. Both players briefly engage and separate.
Brooks (MEM) wraps his left arm around Booker's (PHX) waist and affects his ability to receive the incoming pass.
Booker (PHX) places a hand to Morant's (MEM) side and releases from his body at the end of his drive.
Ayton (PHX) makes contact to Morant's (MEM) head that affects his driving shot attempt.
Johnson (PHX) makes marginal contact with Hill's (MEM) arm during the rebound and doesn't affect his ability to secure the ball.
Rubio (PHX) commits a take foul on Hill (MEM).
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in the frontcourt prior to passing the ball to Johnson (PHX), who is established in the backcourt.
